kdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="grid grid-rows-[auto_auto] min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 min-w-0"><div class="min-w-0 pl-2 py-1.5"><div class="flex items-center gap-2"><button class="group/status flex items-center gap-2 py-1 text-sm transition-colors cursor-pointer text-left text-text-500 hover:text-text-300 flex-1 min-w-0" aria-expanded="false"><div class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 min-w-0" style="opacity: 1;"><span class="truncate text-sm font-base">Viewed 2 files</span><span class="inline-flex transition-transform duration-200 shrink-0 -rotate-90"><div style="width: 12px; height: 12px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><path d="M14.128 7.165a.502.502 0 0 1 .744.67l-4.5 5-.078.07a.5.5 0 0 1-.666-.07l-4.5-5-.06-.082a.501.501 0 0 1 .729-.656l.075.068L10 11.752z"></path></svg></div></span></div></button></div><span class="sr-only" role="status" aria-live="polite">Viewed 2 files</span><div class="grid transition-[grid-template-rows] duration-300 ease-out" style="grid-template-rows: 0fr;"><div class="overflow-hidden min-w-0"></div></div></div></div><div class="row-start-2 col-start-1 relative grid isolate min-w-0"><div class="row-start-1 col-start-1 relative z-[2] min-w-0"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Got it — this is the real homepage. Here's the full audit:</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>✅ What's solid</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Title is good: <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">Notavello — Export AI Conversations as Beautiful PDFs</code></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Meta description names all 6 AIs by name — great for long-tail searches</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Canonical correctly points to <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://notavello.com/</code></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Open Graph + Twitter Card are set</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">robots: index, follow</code> is correct</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">URL structure on all AI card links matches your sitemap (<code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">/exporters/chatgpt/</code> etc.)</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">H1 is static (not JS-injected) — Google will read it fine</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>⚠️ Things to improve</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>H1 is a bit generic.</strong> <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">Turn AI conversations into beautiful PDFs</code> is pretty but not very keyword-rich. Google weighs H1 heavily. Something like <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">Export AI Conversations to PDF — ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini &amp; More</code> would capture more search intent while still sounding good.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>No structured data.</strong> Adding a <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">WebApplication</code> JSON-LD block would help Google understand what the site actually <em>is</em> — a tool, not a blog. Quick win.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">&lt;!--FOOTER--&gt;</code> is a placeholder.</strong> The footer isn't actually injected on this page — there's no real footer HTML here. If Cloudflare Pages isn't doing server-side includes, this comment does nothing and the page has no footer at all in production. Worth verifying.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Missing <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">og:image</code>.</strong> You have OG tags but no <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">og:image</code>. When anyone shares the homepage on social, there'll be no preview image — just text. Even a simple branded card would help.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Twitter description is thinner</strong> than OG — <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">Turn your Claude, ChatGPT, or Gemini conversations</code> drops Copilot, Grok, and Perplexity. Easy to make them match.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>No internal links to Pricing, FAQ, or About</strong> in the body — only in the footer. Those pages need link equity from the homepage too. Even a small "See pricing" line near the CTA would help.</p>
